{"sections":[],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["/documentation/swift/substring/utf16view/enumerated()"]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Returns a sequence of pairs ("},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"n","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"x"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":"), where "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"n"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" represents a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"consecutive integer starting at zero and "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"x"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" represents an element of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the sequence."}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Substring/UTF16View/enumerated()"},"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift","doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Substring","doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Substring/UTF16View"]]},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Instance Method","extendedModule":"Swift","role":"symbol","externalID":"s:STsE10enumerateds18EnumeratedSequenceVyxGyF::SYNTHESIZED::s:Ss9UTF16ViewV","symbolKind":"method","title":"enumerated()","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"enumerated","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:s18EnumeratedSequenceV","text":"EnumeratedSequence","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"Self","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":">","kind":"text"}],"modules":[{"name":"Swift"}]},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"enumerated"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:s18EnumeratedSequenceV","identifier":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/EnumeratedSequence","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"EnumeratedSequence"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Self"},{"kind":"text","text":">"}],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"text":"Return Value","anchor":"return-value","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A sequence of pairs enumerating the sequence.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","level":2,"anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This example enumerates the characters of the string “Swift” and prints"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"each character along with its place in the string."}]},{"code":["for (n, c) in \"Swift\".enumerated() {","    print(\"\\(n): '\\(c)'\")","}","// Prints \"0: 'S'\"","// Prints \"1: 'w'\"","// Prints \"2: 'i'\"","// Prints \"3: 'f'\"","// Prints \"4: 't'\""],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When you enumerate a collection, the integer part of each pair is a counter"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for the enumeration, but is not necessarily the index of the paired value."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"These counters can be used as indices only in instances of zero-based,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"integer-indexed collections, such as "},{"code":"Array","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"ContiguousArray","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". For"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"other collections the counters may be out of range or of the wrong type"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to use as an index. To iterate over the elements of a collection with its"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"indices, use the "},{"code":"zip(_:_:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" function.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This example iterates over the indices and elements of a set, building a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"list consisting of indices of names with five or fewer letters."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let names: Set = [\"Sofia\", \"Camilla\", \"Martina\", \"Mateo\", \"Nicolás\"]","var shorterIndices: [Set<String>.Index] = []","for (i, name) in zip(names.indices, names) {","    if name.count <= 5 {","        shorterIndices.append(i)","    }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Now that the ","type":"text"},{"code":"shorterIndices","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" array holds the indices of the shorter","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"names in the ","type":"text"},{"code":"names","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" set, you can use those indices to access elements in","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the set.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["for i in shorterIndices {","    print(names[i])","}","// Prints \"Sofia\"","// Prints \"Mateo\""]},{"type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"O(1)"}]}],"style":"note","name":"Complexity"}],"kind":"content"}],"references":{"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Substring/UTF16View":{"role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"UTF16View","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"/documentation/swift/substring/utf16view","identifier":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Substring/UTF16View","title":"Substring.UTF16View","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"UTF16View","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[]},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Substring/UTF16View/enumerated()":{"role":"symbol","url":"/documentation/swift/substring/utf16view/enumerated()","identifier":"doc://com.apple.Swi